<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="185" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[178,1085,617,762]" pageId="22" pageNumber="185">
C o m m e n t: The original description is based on a male 
<typeStatus box="[864,953,617,639]" pageId="22" pageNumber="185">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<specimenCount pageId="22" pageNumber="185" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">twelve paratypes</specimenCount>
from Da Shennongjia in 
<collectingRegion box="[521,583,648,670]" country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="22" pageNumber="185">Hubei</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="WILLERS J" box="[597,763,648,670]" pageId="22" pageNumber="185" pagination="287 - 309" refId="ref12722" refString="WILLERS J. (2001 a): Neue asiatische Arten der Gattung Paederus FABRICIUS s. l. aus der Sammlung des Naturhistorischen Museums Basel (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Entomologica Basiliensia 23: 287 - 309." type="journal article" year="2001">WILLERS 2001a</bibRefCitation>
). The species was subsequently reported from additional localities in Shennongjia County by LI &amp; ZHOU (2007) and 
<bibRefCitation author="PENG Z &amp; LI L" box="[178,396,709,731]" pageId="22" pageNumber="185" pagination="143 - 153" refId="ref12482" refString="PENG Z., LI L. - Z. &amp; M. - J. ZHAO (2015): New data on the subgenus Harpopaederus of the genus Paederus (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae) of mainland China. - ZooKeys 495: 143 - 153." type="journal article" year="2015">PENG et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
. The record from 
<collectingRegion box="[618,700,709,731]" country="China" name="Shaanxi" pageId="22" pageNumber="185">Shaanxi</collectingRegion>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="SMETANA A" box="[753,936,709,731]" pageId="22" pageNumber="185" pagination="579 - 624" refId="ref12671" refString="SMETANA A. (2004): Subfamily Paederinae FLEMING, 1821. - In: LOBL I. &amp; A. SMETANA (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 2. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphylinoidea. - Apollo Books, Stenstrup: 579 - 624." type="book chapter" year="2004">SMETANA (2004)</bibRefCitation>
is based on misidentified material. The currently known distribution is illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[912,980,740,761]" captionStart="Map 3" captionStartId="5.[178,223,991,1012]" captionTargetBox="[185,1078,212,982]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[185,1078,212,982]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Map 3: Distributions of Harpopaederus species in the Qinling Shan and the Daba Shan in Shaanxi, Hubei, North Sichuan, and Chongqing (some doubtful female-based literature records omitted): Paederus xui (filled diamonds); P. konfuzius (open stars); P. brevior (triangles); P. lineodenticulatus (open circles); P. cultellatus (filled triangle); P. apfelsinicus (filled circles); P. multidenticulatus (open triangle)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414052/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="185">Map 3</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[178,1086,779,1016]" pageId="22" pageNumber="185">
This species is characterized particularly by the pronounced dimorphism of the head (larger, more transverse, and with more distinctly marked posterior angles in males than in females) and of the mandibles (longer, curved, and with the molar teeth distinctly separated in males), by the coloration (legs blackish; antennomeres IV-XI apically more or less distinctly infuscate; preapical palpomere of the maxillary palpi apically infuscate), the morphology of the aedeagus, the broadly semi-transparent and strongly convex posterior margin of the female tergite VIII, and by the shape of the female sternite VIII. For illustrations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="WILLERS" authorityYear="2001" box="[373,522,994,1015]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Paederus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apfelsinicus">
<emphasis box="[373,522,994,1015]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="185">P. apfelsinicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation author="WILLERS J" box="[567,747,994,1016]" pageId="22" pageNumber="185" pagination="287 - 309" refId="ref12722" refString="WILLERS J. (2001 a): Neue asiatische Arten der Gattung Paederus FABRICIUS s. l. aus der Sammlung des Naturhistorischen Museums Basel (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Entomologica Basiliensia 23: 287 - 309." type="journal article" year="2001">WILLERS (2001a)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
